TsuboDB
=========

TsuboDB is a client for AniDB's UDP API. (http://anidb.net/)
Intended to create a simple, automated flow for easily watching anime and
recording it to an AniDB profile.

Originally based on PyAniDB. (https://github.com/xyzz/pyanidb)

Installation
============

For manual installation; run:

  ./setup.py build
  sudo ./setup.py install

Usage
=====

usage: tsubodb.py [options]

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -u USERNAME, --username USERNAME
                        AniDB username.
  -p PASSWORD, --password PASSWORD
                        AniDB password.
  -s SUFFIX, --suffix SUFFIX
                        File suffixes to include when scanning directories.
  -w, --watched         Mark files watched.
  --fetch-mylist        Re-download mylist into db.
  --database-file DATABASE_FILE
                        Database file location.
  --anime-dir ANIME_DIR
                        Anime base dir for file scanning.
  --playnext            Play next episode then mark watched.
  --scan [SCAN]         Scan dir for new files, and import them. Defaults to
                        anime-dir, or specify.
  --force-rehash        Force rehashing files for scan.
  --force-recheck       Force rechecking with anidb files for scan (use after
                        adding files to anidb through Avdump2)
  --fill-database       Fill any missing files or Mylists
  --fill-mylist         Get/Add MyList for all files.
  --vote VOTE           Rate an anime by aid.

Example:

TODO
after setting up the config file to point at your video player and anime
directory:

tsubodb.py --scan

tsubodb.py --playnext
